case insensitive 不區分大小寫
Treats the input as multiple lines 將輸入視為多行
treats newline characters as stop characters 將換行符視為停止字符
excluding 不包括
whitespace 空格
Returns the start and end indices of each submatch in the specified variable 傳回指定變數中每個子符合的起始索引和結束索引
occurrences 發生

approximate 近似
literally 字面上地


===============================================
regexp ?options? pattern ?match sub1 sub2.....?

Option - Description
-nocase --> Perform a case insensitive matching
-line --> Treats the input as multiple lines, allowing ^ and $ to match the beginning and end of each line.
-linestop --> When used with -line, treats newline characters as stop characters, excluding them from the match
-expanded --> Allows whitespace and comments within the rebular expression for improved readability
-indices varName --> Returns the start and end indices of each submatch in the specified variable
-all --> Matches all occurrences of the regular expression

-inline --> Returns a list of data that otherwise would be placed in match variables
-start index --> Start the matching process at the specified index
-about --> Enables approximate matching
-exact --> Disables approximage matching. Useful if pattern contains characters with special meaning we want to be matched literally.
-- --> Signals the end of the options. Useful if the string starts with '-'
